{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771347645,"nonce":"RIj3pZeYc41ye9Brk4EWCQohp7s=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87rqYob","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/221","origin":"github"},"title":"Agents should verify issue number matches task before committing","message":"## Problem\n\nAgents sometimes latch onto the wrong issue number when starting work. This happens when:\n\n1. A planning session occurs inside an existing worktree for a different task. The plan\n   inherits the branch context and bakes in the wrong issue number.\n2. A fresh agent receives the plan and trusts the issue number without verifying it.\n3. The conversation's initial `gitStatus` shows a branch like `feature/issue-217`, and\n   the agent assumes it is relevant to the current task.\n\nThe issue-first policy says \"no code without a ticket,\" but there is no explicit step\nrequiring agents to **verify the issue title matches the task they are implementing**\nbefore committing. Agents treat the issue number as given rather than cross-checking.\n\n### Observed impact\n\n- Commits land on the wrong branch with the wrong `Closes #N` reference\n- PRs get created against unrelated issues\n- Cleanup requires cherry-picking, force-pushing, and creating new branches/PRs\n\n### Proposed fix\n\nAdd a verification step to the workflow instructions (CLAUDE.md and peer files) such as:\n\n\u003e Before your first commit, verify that the issue you are working under matches your\n\u003e current task: run `gh issue view \u003cN\u003e --json title` and confirm the title is related.\n\u003e If the issue does not match, stop and create or find the correct issue before proceeding.\n\nThis could go in the \"Issue-First Policy\" section of each instruction file, or as a\npre-commit checklist item.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}